data.title: So fetch! Lindsay Lohan and Tina Fey REUNITE at Mean Girls premiere in NYC alongside new cast featured in musical version of the iconic film
data.meta_description: Lindsay Lohan and Tina Fey reunited at the star-studded Mean Girls premiere in New York City on Monday alongside other cast member ahead of the musical comedy's release.
data.text:
Lindsay Lohan and Tina Fey reunited at the star-studded Mean Girls premiere in New York City on Monday alongside other cast members.

The Freaky Friday actress, 37 - who recently was seen for the first time with five-month-old son Luai - notably starred in the original 2004 film portraying the role of Cady Heron, while the SNL alum, 53, had taken on the role of Ms. Norbury.

The upcoming musical comedy is slated to hit theaters later this month on January 12, and is based on the Broadway musical of the same name.

Lohan was effortlessly radiant wearing a fitted black dress that contained cutouts on the sides. Fabric at the front was held together by a sparkling, silver belt that wrapped around her midriff.

She slipped into a pair of closed-toed, black heels that were secured with thin straps that wrapped around her ankles.

She accessorized her look by adding a pair of dangly, silver earrings and also carried a sleek, black clutch bag in her hand that had a shimmering, silver embellishment on the front.

Her long locks were parted to the side, and cascaded down past her shoulders in elegant waves.

Lindsay's makeup was glammed up for the big event, and comprised of a layer of mascara to her lashes as well as a dark, smoky shadow around her eyes.

A light pink blush was added to her cheekbones, while a satin, rosy pink tint was worn on her lips for a finishing touch.

Lohan held a big smile on her face as she struck a variety of poses on the pink carpet, and at one point, turned away from the cameras to show off the backless portion of the gown.

She was spotted crossing paths with her former co-star, Tina Fey, who was also dressed to impress for the festivities.

The stars held excited expressions on their faces and jumped in to share a quick embrace as they reunited - nearly twenty years after the original Mean Girls film was released.

Lindsay and Tina paused for a few memorable photos together at the star-studded screening before heading into the main venue.

Lindsay also opened up about Mean Girls with Entertainment Tonight on the pink carpet on Monday, and gushed, 'It's stood the test of time.'

'I feel really grateful. I mean, it's not very often that you have all these movies that do that,' she continued.

'Mean Girls really opened the doors for a lot of things going on in schools. I think it's also a really fun movie, so it's really a blessing.'

Fey donned a fitted, black and white-polka dot dress that also contained colorful butterfly and bug details throughout the material.

The ensemble contained a belt with a silver buckle at the front that wrapped around her waist and was partially unfastened around the collar.

The actress and comedian slipped into a pair of closed-toed, black pumps that coincided with the color scheme of her outfit for the evening.

Her brunette locks were parted to the side and flowed down in light waves to brush the tips of her shoulders.

Tina added a pair of silver-hooped earrings, as well as a few rings and a dainty necklace to accessorize the look.

She notably wrote the screenplay for the 2024 adaptation, and also reprised her role of Ms. Norbury in the musical comedy. Both Fey and Lorne Michaels produced the upcoming movie.

The duo also took time to take another picture with Lohan while walking the pink carpet at the AMC Lincoln Square Theater.

Renee Rapp - who took on the role of Regina George - turned heads wearing a fitted, corset-styled dress that contained hues of both pink and black.

A thigh-high slit could be seen on the left side of the eye-catching ensemble for a sultry flare.

The actress also donned a pair of chic, black heels and allowed her blonde locks to flow down past her shoulders.

Rapp opted for minimal accessories to allow her outfit to be the main focal point, and wore a pair of pearl earrings as well as a few silver rings on each of her hands.

Megan Thee Stallion also wowed at the event, and donned a figure-hugging, purple mermaid-style dress.

The halter-styled gown contained a large cutout on the front which was bordered with lavender-colored embellishments.

Her platinum blonde locks were parted to the side, and effortlessly flowed down in elegant curls.

The Savage hitmaker added a pair of sparkling earrings as well as flashy rings on each of her hands.

The performer's makeup was glammed up, and comprised of glamorous lashes as well as a light, smoky shadow around her eyes.

A warm blush and contour was added to better accentuate her cheekbones, while a nude-colored tint was worn on her lips and bordered by a darker lipliner.

Megan later crossed paths with Renee, and the pair stopped to take an assortment of lighthearted photos together on the pink carpet.

They notably collaborated on the track, Not My Fault, which was released last month in December.

In one image, the Mean Girls star playfully stuck her tongue out while the rapper blew a kiss towards the camera.

Another picture showed Renee holding a small smile on her face, while the singer flashed a peace sign with her hand.

Angourie Rice - who took on the role of Cady Heron in the film - put on a dazzling display wearing a sparkling, peach-colored dress that contained a plunging, V-neck cut.

The ensemble was held up with thin straps that wrapped around her shoulders, and flowed down to brush the ground.

The star's locks were parted to the side, and effortlessly cascaded down past her shoulders in bouncy curls.

She added a dainty, silver-chained necklace to accessorize her look for the special premiere as well as glittering rings.

A pink blush and eye shadow was added to her glammed up makeup, while a glossy, light pink tint was worn on her lips for a finishing touch.

Angourie was seen crossing paths with Lindsay - who had also originally played Cady in the original 2004 film.

The two stars held cheerful smiles on their faces as they excitedly stopped to take a few pictures together at the event.

Rice also briefly ran into fellow co-star, Tina Fey, and the pair also paused for a memorable snap together.

Avantika Vandanapu - who played the character of Karen Shetty - was an ethereal beauty wearing an off-white gown that had glittering, gold patterns throughout the fabric.

The dress also contained a matching cape that had similar details embroidered onto the sheer fabric that was wrapped around her neck.

Her locks were swept up and styled into a chic up do, allowing a few loose strands to border the left side of her face.

A pair of large, sparkling earrings were added to accessorize the glamorous look, while a few rings were added on her hands.

Bebe Wood - who portrayed Gretchen Wieners - stunned in a retro-themed ensemble that comprised of a strapless, black velvet dress that contained both white and pink fabric on the bottom portion.

She also slipped into a pair of white lace tights as well as black heels that had a gold, bow embellishment on top.

A black, velvet choker was added to accessorize her look, while a pair of of small, dangly earrings were also worn.

Her hair was parted to the side, and flowed down naturally in light waves past her shoulders.

Jane Krakowski was also in attendance and wowed wearing a black dress that contained a fitted bodice and a skirt that stopped just above her knees.

Shimmering, silver embellishments bordered the neckline and thick straps that wrapped around her shoulders.

The 30 Rock star slipped into a pair of closed-toed, black heels to coincide with the color scheme of the outfit.

Her blonde locks were parted in the middle, and effortlessly flowed down past her shoulders in elegant waves.

She crossed paths with her former 30 Rock co-star, Tina Fey, and the pair also took time for a quick photo session together.

Auli'i Cravalho showed off her stunning frame wearing a black, strapless dress that had satin fabric draped around a portion of the ensemble.

The Crush star donned a pair of open-toed, black heels and also carried a small, black clutch in her hand.

The back portion of the gown a strip of red fabric that offered a pop of color to the monochromatic look.

She added various rings on each of her hands that offered a flashy flare to the outfit, as well as a gold bracelet and earrings.

Busy Philipps - who exuded 1950s glamour - donned a strapless, light blue dress with black polka dot details.

A large bow could be seen at the back of the strapless ensemble and the actress - who took on the role of Mrs. George - wore a pair of open-toed, black pumps.

The beauty also added a pair of black, elbow-length gloves and easily carried a black clutch bag in her hand.

Her blonde locks were parted in the middle, and pulled back into a chic up do, preventing any loose strands from falling onto her face.

Busy was seen running into Birdie Silverstein at the premiere and who also exuded a retro flare.

She wore a white and blue-patterned minidress that contained a high neck and slipped into a pair of white pumps.

Her locks were teased to offer volume and fell down in light curls while a blue ribbon was also placed in her hair. The two held big smiles on their faces while posing for a few photos together at the event.

Jon Hamm was dapper as he also stopped by the premiere, and was joined by his wife, Anna Osceola, who put on a radiant display.

The Mad Man actor - who took on the role of Coach Carr in the film - donned a dark navy suit that comprised of slacks and a double-breasted blazer.

Underneath, the star wore a plain navy shirt and slipped into a pair of dark brown shoes to complete his look.

His wife was beautiful in a hot pink minidress that contained cutouts on the side and had a floral embellishment on the front.

She donned a pair of open-toed, pink heels that were secured with straps that wrapped around her ankles.

Her brunette locks were partially pulled back away from her face, and flowed down naturally past her shoulders.

The lovebirds stood closely together as they paused for pictures while standing on the pink carpet.

Paige DeSorbo turned heads wearing a strapless, black velvet romper that contained pink ruched fabric at the bodice.

She slipped into a pair of sheer, black tights as well as closed-toed heels to complete her look.

Her dark locks were parted to the side, and effortlessly flowed down in elegant curls that brushed past her shoulders.

Paige joined Hannah Berner on the pink carpet who wowed in a fitted, white dress that contained a pink trim on the neckline as well as a thin, pink belt.

Rachel Dratch dazzled in a black, sequin minidress that contained a hem that stopped just above her knees.

The SNL alum opted for a pair of black tights as well as black heels that contained sparkling, silver embellishments on top.

Christopher Briney - who portrayed Aaron Samuels - was dapper wearing a satin, black suit which he paired with a black shirt underneath and sleek dress shoes.

The actor was accompanied by Isabel Machado who wowed wearing a green dress that contained ruffled details on the neckline as well as the thigh-high slit on the left side.

Daniel Franzese - who portrayed Damien in the 2004 film - also stopped by the premiere and sported a silver, leather jacket that had a teddy bear on the front.

He also donned a pair of black pants as well as silver sneakers to complete his look for the night.

Before the official screening of Mean Girls commenced, stars gathered together for a photo, including Renee Rapp, Lorne Michaels, Tina Fey and also Lindsay Lohan.

In another image, Rapp, Fey, Michaels and Lohan also were joined by Angourie Rice as well as Bebe Wood for a memorable moment.

Rice and Lohan also paused for a snap with Christopher Briney before heading inside the main theater on Monday.

Lastly, the cast and crew also came together for a fun photo as they all posed on the pink carpet.
